Mr. Durbin presented no danger
to the city's female population.

18:38.230 --> 18:42.223
The court ordered Mr. Durbin to
undergo 12 sessions with Dr. Burnhardt.

18:43.169 --> 18:45.296
But last week, with
three sessions to go,

18:45.371 --> 18:49.364
Burnhardt took Mr. Durbin
on as a private patient.

18:49.442 --> 18:50.966
Meaning everything
that Durbin tells him

18:51.043 --> 18:53.534
is covered by doctor-patient privilege.

18:53.612 --> 18:55.443
Well, this started
with the session

18:55.514 --> 18:59.951
Durbin had two days
after Phoebe's murder.

19:00.019 --> 19:02.385
He might've told the shrink
something about the murder.

19:02.455 --> 19:06.289
Something that contradicted
his rosy psych evaluation.

19:07.793 --> 19:12.389
Maybe Burnhardt turned Keith into a
private patient to protect himself.

19:12.698 --> 19:15.690
I'll ask him. In front
of the grand jury.

19:20.439 --> 19:23.237
After Mr. Durbin pled guilty to assault,

19:23.309 --> 19:26.506
I was asked to prepare
a psychological evaluation.

19:27.112 --> 19:30.639
I felt then that Mr. Durbin
posed no danger to women.

19:31.350 --> 19:33.147
I still believe that.

19:33.219 --> 19:36.450
Let's talk about your session two
days after Phoebe Morton's murder.

19:36.522 --> 19:40.481
I can't. Mr. Durbin became
my private patient that day.

19:40.993 --> 19:42.824
Doctor-patient
privilege attached,

19:42.895 --> 19:45.159
his sessions
became confidential.

19:46.765 --> 19:50.223
Only the patient can waive
privilege, isn't that right?

19:50.669 --> 19:55.231
If he chose to, Mr. Durbin could
tell us what he said to you that day.

19:58.310 --> 19:59.402
Yes.

19:59.678 --> 20:02.977
Lf, in the future, Mr. Durbin
confesses he killed Ms. Morton,

20:03.048 --> 20:05.778
he could reveal he made
an admission to you,

20:05.851 --> 20:08.046
one that makes your evaluation of him

20:08.120 --> 20:11.317
as posing no danger
to women seem incompetent.

20:11.557 --> 20:14.287
Unless, of course, the
information came from you

20:14.360 --> 20:16.521
before Mr. Durbin
confesses.

20:16.595 --> 20:18.256
But I can't
violate privilege.

20:18.330 --> 20:20.195
An argument
can be made

20:20.266 --> 20:24.396
that anything Mr. Durbin told you
is part of court-ordered therapy,

20:24.770 --> 20:27.102
not subject
to confidentiality.

20:28.741 --> 20:29.799
It could be
viewed that way.

20:29.875 --> 20:32.810
I'm asking you
to view it that way.

20:36.448 --> 20:40.009
During that session, two days
after Ms. Morton's murder,

20:40.653 --> 20:44.612
did Mr. Durbin say
anything about Ms. Morton?

20:48.227 --> 20:50.559
He saw the newspaper on my desk

20:51.030 --> 20:54.488
with a photo of Ms. Morton.
He said, "That could be me. "

20:54.567 --> 20:58.469
Did you think he meant he himself
could be the murder victim?

20:58.537 --> 21:01.506
No. I knew right away
he meant the killer.

21:02.708 --> 21:05.370
Keith has always been
filled with foreboding

21:05.444 --> 21:09.403
that his sexual issues would
inevitably lead to serious trouble.

21:10.649 --> 21:13.049
At that moment,
it occurred to me

21:13.452 --> 21:16.819
what he'd been trying to
tell me during our sessions.

21:17.122 --> 21:21.388
That he felt himself
fated to kill.

21:25.831 --> 21:27.628
I never forced Talia.

21:28.367 --> 21:32.827
She freaked out and got caught in
the rope, and wrenched her shoulder.

21:34.373 --> 21:37.672
I never meant to hurt her.
I never hurt anyone.

21:37.743 --> 21:41.839
You tried to put a slipknot around
her neck, but not to choke her?

21:42.381 --> 21:45.646
It's the idea of it.

21:46.185 --> 21:49.552
The idea of choking
a woman excites you.

21:49.622 --> 21:53.615
No, it's just the way
a woman looks like that.

21:53.692 --> 21:56.661
On her stomach, bound and
gagged, in her bra and panties?

21:56.729 --> 21:59.323
White bra and panties,
they should be white.

21:59.398 --> 22:01.263
Right, with her right
ankle tied to her neck...

22:01.333 --> 22:03.563
No, it's her left ankle.

22:05.971 --> 22:09.907
Yes, my mistake. Your way
of doing things is unique.

22:11.677 --> 22:15.340
Dr. Burnhardt testified when you
saw Ms. Morton in the newspaper,

22:15.414 --> 22:17.348
you said,
"That could be me. "

22:17.416 --> 22:21.682
I wanted to explain that I
meant, if I wasn't in therapy,

22:22.087 --> 22:25.113
if I didn't have self-control,
bad things could happen.

22:25.190 --> 22:27.090
You could be that killer.
That's what you meant,

22:27.159 --> 22:28.251
you could lose control.

22:28.327 --> 22:30.192
I won't lose control.
Dr. Burnhardt testified

22:30.262 --> 22:31.820
you were filled
with foreboding,

22:31.897 --> 22:33.888
you felt fated
to kill someday.

22:33.966 --> 22:34.955
I won't ever
let that happen.

22:35.034 --> 22:37.730
Where do you get that sense
of yourself as a killer?

22:41.907 --> 22:43.841
I don't know. Do you have
fantasies about killing?

22:43.909 --> 22:45.035
No, no, I don't.

22:45.110 --> 22:47.738
Then what is the source
of your apprehension?

22:47.813 --> 22:50.577
Mr. Durbin, it must
come from somewhere.

22:50.683 --> 22:54.119
I can't. I don't know, I don't know.

22:56.188 --> 22:58.418
You don't have
to answer anymore.

22:59.992 --> 23:02.859
I don't want to answer
any more questions.

23:02.928 --> 23:05.658
There's no need,
Mr. Durbin. Thank you.

23:07.266 --> 23:09.757
This, his
testimony here,

23:09.835 --> 23:13.566
when he specified the bra
and panties should be white,

23:13.639 --> 23:16.767
none of his victims wore
white bra and panties.

23:16.842 --> 23:17.831
Luck of the draw.

23:17.910 --> 23:20.105
Except he's very rigid
in his preferences.

23:20.179 --> 23:23.774
He made his victims undress. It
wouldn't have required much more effort

23:23.849 --> 23:26.818
to ask them to put on
a white bra and panties.

23:26.885 --> 23:29.752
All the lingerie we found
in his apartment was white.

23:29.822 --> 23:34.657
And here, when you said right
ankle, instead of left, you...

23:35.094 --> 23:37.085
You made a mistake,
and he let it pass.

23:37.162 --> 23:38.925
No, he corrected me.

23:39.598 --> 23:42.761
Without ridiculing you. You
know, the Jake in the letters,

23:42.835 --> 23:45.133
he would have berated
you for incompetence.

23:46.739 --> 23:49.173
Your sense of timing,
Detective...

23:50.042 --> 23:52.237
We might have
made a mistake.

23:55.147 --> 23:59.049
Grand jury disagrees. Indicted
Durbin on five counts of murder.

24:30.749 --> 24:33.741
I just got the "proceed with
caution" signal from the Captain.

24:33.819 --> 24:36.185
Once the DA has a
suspect in their mitts,

24:36.255 --> 24:38.280
they don't like
giving him up.

24:38.357 --> 24:41.451
Look, the third victim,
Christina Paulen,

24:41.527 --> 24:43.461
she changed jobs three
months before her murder.

24:43.529 --> 24:46.965
She used to work on Spring.
She would take the D Train

24:47.032 --> 24:51.469
down to West 4th and
change for the C to Spring.

24:51.937 --> 24:54.929
She changed at the
West 4th Street station.

24:55.407 --> 24:57.170
The same as the first two victims.

24:57.242 --> 25:00.769
But the fourth victim, Darlene
Jorif, she drove to work.

25:08.353 --> 25:11.516
She bought her car a month
before she was killed.

25:13.058 --> 25:15.253
Well, if she used
to take the subway,

25:15.327 --> 25:19.229
she would have been transferring
at West 4th to get to work.

25:21.266 --> 25:24.064
Why Marcia Waverly? She took
the PATH train from New Jersey.

25:24.136 --> 25:26.502
Now, she would have transferred
at West 4th to get up to Lexington.

25:26.572 --> 25:30.668
You see, that's where he picked
up their scent, at West 4th.

25:31.043 --> 25:33.978
He followed them,
he learned their schedules,

25:34.046 --> 25:35.411
and when he was
ready, he struck.

25:35.480 --> 25:38.540
Another commuter
or a Transit Authority worker.

25:39.017 --> 25:40.541
Cassandra Darcy,
our near miss,

25:40.619 --> 25:43.645
she transfers at the 14th
Street station to get to work.

25:43.722 --> 25:46.213
That leaves Phoebe
out in the cold.

25:46.959 --> 25:48.051
But the night
she was killed,

25:48.126 --> 25:49.957
she filled her MetroCard
at the 14th Street station,

25:50.028 --> 25:52.792
and that's how she got to
Battery Park. She took the subway.

25:52.865 --> 25:55.129
West 4th Street,
14th Street,

25:55.200 --> 25:58.727
match up the dates to her work
history, maybe we get a suspect.

26:01.974 --> 26:03.532
Do you have any idea
how many people pass

26:03.609 --> 26:05.600
through this station
any given day? It's a lot.

26:05.677 --> 26:08.475
There was somebody else working
with you that night, a Frank...

26:08.547 --> 26:11.175
McNare, Frank McNare. Frank!

26:11.750 --> 26:15.186
Now, there's one who might
remember. He notices things.

26:16.288 --> 26:19.052
Hey, Frank, they're asking about
a girl murdered in Battery Park

26:19.124 --> 26:21.092
a couple of weeks ago.
She was in the station.

26:21.159 --> 26:23.127
You remember
seeing her?

26:25.530 --> 26:28.829
I was wondering when you'd
get around to talking with us.

26:28.901 --> 26:32.803
Yeah. I recognized her when I
saw her picture in the newspaper.

26:34.273 --> 26:36.400
You noticed her
that night?

26:36.842 --> 26:40.801
There's not much else to do down
here but notice the pretty girls.

26:40.879 --> 26:45.316
I saw her, I said to myself,
"That is a pretty girl. "

26:45.384 --> 26:48.353
Do you remember anybody
talking to her or following her?

26:48.420 --> 26:51.685
No. But she got a phone
call just before she left.

26:53.425 --> 26:55.757
Maybe we should be
writing this down.

26:55.827 --> 26:56.816
Good idea.

26:59.064 --> 27:02.761
You said that she got a phone
call just before she left.

27:03.268 --> 27:04.257
Right.

27:04.336 --> 27:06.270
And did you see
anyone following her?

27:06.738 --> 27:09.332
Your partner already
asked me that.

27:09.408 --> 27:11.501
You know, you should
write down your questions

27:11.576 --> 27:13.840
and mark them off
as you ask them.

27:13.912 --> 27:16.403
That way you won't
repeat yourself.

27:17.916 --> 27:19.349
Good idea.

27:19.418 --> 27:21.648
We gotta go.
Shift's changing.

27:25.390 --> 27:27.915
Arrogant would be
an understatement.

27:30.262 --> 27:31.752
"Pretty girls. "

27:34.399 --> 27:38.426
He articulates his "T's,"
just like the 911 caller.

27:39.471 --> 27:42.907
It's a pronunciation
idiosyncrasy.

27:42.975 --> 27:46.672
It's picked up by children
when they learn to talk.

27:47.879 --> 27:49.642
Children like Keith.

27:49.881 --> 27:51.576
Frank, he had
red sideburns,

27:51.650 --> 27:55.518
got brown hair and a red
beard, just like Keith.

27:57.189 --> 27:59.749
It's unusual,
and it's genetic.

27:59.825 --> 28:01.554
It's passed on
from father to son.

28:02.728 --> 28:04.719
We just met
Keith's dad.

28:10.035 --> 28:14.495
Frank McNare divorced Keith's
mother in 1978, when Keith was eight.

28:14.573 --> 28:16.632
They were living
up in New Rochelle.

28:16.708 --> 28:20.269
McNare moved to Queens, he got
a job at the Transit Authority.

28:20.345 --> 28:24.714
Now, by 1988, he was working
at the West 4th Street station.

28:24.783 --> 28:28.879
So far, Mr. McNare seems nothing
more than a victim of coincidence.

28:28.954 --> 28:31.889
We've tracked his history. Not
only was he around for the killings,

28:31.957 --> 28:35.415
we can even explain
why he stopped in 1992.

28:35.494 --> 28:39.692
He got married that year. Now,
if his wife was a true masochist,

28:39.765 --> 28:43.223
someone who would let him act
out his sadistic fantasies,

28:43.301 --> 28:45.201
he wouldn't need
unwilling partners.

28:45.270 --> 28:47.932
But when his wife died
last year of breast cancer,

28:48.006 --> 28:50.031
he would have started
hunting for new partners.

28:50.108 --> 28:53.009
And the '96 murder,
if he was married...

28:53.078 --> 28:56.946
His wife had her first bout
of cancer back then.

28:57.015 --> 29:00.041
She was sick for a year, she
wouldn't have been up for his games.

29:00.118 --> 29:03.610
But if, as you say, Mr.
McNare's a sexual sadist,

29:03.688 --> 29:07.055
that's something he and his
son would have in common.

29:07.626 --> 29:11.585
And sexual sadism is not
an inherited trait, is it?

29:12.531 --> 29:13.555
No.

29:14.332 --> 29:18.496
I don't know why Keith has the same
sexual hard-wiring as his father.

29:18.570 --> 29:22.973
You have no evidence what Mr.
McNare's sexual proclivities are.

29:23.041 --> 29:24.941
His ex-wife would know.

29:28.346 --> 29:30.405
Keith hasn't seen Frank
since he was eight.

29:30.482 --> 29:32.848
Why are you
interested in him?

29:36.688 --> 29:39.782
Frank's sexual interests
when you were married,

29:40.292 --> 29:44.353
did they include bondage
or pain, even in mild forms?

29:44.429 --> 29:46.795
No, our sex life
was very conventional.

29:46.865 --> 29:50.596
Mrs. Durbin, you know
what Keith has admitted to.

29:51.303 --> 29:54.966
Now, his behavior
has a source.

29:55.040 --> 29:56.803
Maybe it was something
in his childhood.

30:01.746 --> 30:03.646
You remember something.

30:03.882 --> 30:06.817
It was such
a childish thing.

30:08.487 --> 30:12.651
And I yelled at him for it,
I shouldn't have. He was seven.

30:14.192 --> 30:15.284
I came into my room

30:15.360 --> 30:19.194
and found that he'd dressed his
teddy bear in my underthings.

30:19.865 --> 30:22.197
It was on the floor
on its stomach.

30:22.267 --> 30:26.033
I know it's normal for
children to be curious, but...

30:27.973 --> 30:29.133
There's something else?

30:29.207 --> 30:33.200
He had tied a string, a blue
string, around the teddy bear's leg.

30:37.249 --> 30:39.979
You remember where
he'd been that day?

30:40.051 --> 30:42.383
With Frank. Frank was
a claims adjuster.

30:42.454 --> 30:46.788
Saturday afternoons he'd take
photos of damaged cars and homes.

30:46.858 --> 30:49.019
Sometimes he'd take
Keith with him.

30:49.094 --> 30:51.085
What kind of camera did he use?

30:51.163 --> 30:52.528
A Polaroid.

30:53.331 --> 30:57.995
And while Frank was with clients,
Keith would wait in the car.

30:58.703 --> 30:59.795
Yes.

31:01.139 --> 31:03.699
Keith might've found
something in his father's car.

31:03.775 --> 31:05.402
Say, a photo.

31:05.477 --> 31:07.468
Something that made
a deep impression,

31:07.546 --> 31:10.913
so deep that he recreated
it with his teddy bear.

31:10.982 --> 31:12.108
Photo of what?

31:12.184 --> 31:16.086
We know Jake likes to take pictures
of his victims bound and gagged.

31:16.154 --> 31:20.887
But in 1977, 12 years before
the first Body By Jake murder?

31:21.526 --> 31:24.120
The first one that
Jake took credit for.

31:24.196 --> 31:25.185
Here.

31:25.263 --> 31:27.163
"Kimberly Lange,
19, disappeared

31:27.232 --> 31:30.133
"from a parking lot
in New Rochelle in 1977."

31:30.202 --> 31:32.727
Her remains were
identified in 1983.

31:33.638 --> 31:35.765
She's slender,
with long dark hair.

31:35.840 --> 31:36.829
Jake's type.

31:37.108 --> 31:39.235
ME found ligature
marks on her left ankle

31:39.311 --> 31:43.179
and two strands of blue and white
polyester embedded in her wrist.

31:43.248 --> 31:45.910
Assuming that 7-year-old Keith
did see a photo of the victim,

31:45.984 --> 31:50.080
from that one instance, he developed
a full-blown sexual obsession?

31:50.155 --> 31:53.318
Well, the image of a
terrified, half-naked woman,

31:57.028 --> 31:58.086
it's shocking.

31:58.163 --> 32:02.395
The boy, he would have known
that it was secret and forbidden.

32:02.467 --> 32:05.368
It would've imprinted
itself on his psyche.

32:06.037 --> 32:07.129
Somehow he figured out

32:07.205 --> 32:10.732
that the photo that he saw was
of a woman about to be murdered.

32:10.809 --> 32:13.903
Well, it was front-page
news when they ID'ed her.

32:14.913 --> 32:18.974
And they describe her as having a
birthmark over her right shoulder blade.

32:19.050 --> 32:20.039
The photo that Keith
would've seen,

32:20.118 --> 32:23.519
it would've been of her lying
on her stomach, bound and gagged,

32:23.588 --> 32:25.453
birthmark would have been
visible, he would have seen it.

32:25.523 --> 32:29.357
He was 13 when she was found, he
would've remembered the birthmark,

32:29.427 --> 32:31.987
he would've figured out
his father killed her.

32:32.063 --> 32:33.655
If he knows, why not say something?

32:33.732 --> 32:35.495
Well, we'll ask him.

32:35.934 --> 32:39.233
And let his lawyer know we're
looking at other suspects?

32:39.304 --> 32:42.637
Have you even collected DNA
samples from Frank McNare yet?

32:42.707 --> 32:44.197
Get us the paper,
we'll get on it.

32:44.276 --> 32:46.608
It's better to cast
a wider net.

32:46.945 --> 32:50.244
We might not want Frank
knowing that he's a suspect.

32:51.049 --> 32:52.983
They said they're gonna
take about 10 minutes.

32:53.051 --> 32:54.040
Yeah.

32:54.119 --> 32:58.886
Mr. McNare, you here
to volunteer your DNA?

32:58.957 --> 33:00.584
This still about that girl?

33:00.659 --> 33:02.684
We took samples from
every guy at her work,

33:02.761 --> 33:05.924
now we're doing the same
along the route she traveled.

33:05.997 --> 33:08.363
No one's turned us
down yet. How about it?

33:10.869 --> 33:13.736
The big DNA dragnet, huh?

33:15.607 --> 33:18.132
This what you guys do
when you run out of ideas?

33:18.209 --> 33:19.642
Pretty much.

33:19.978 --> 33:23.607
Now, there's a questionnaire
to fill out for every sample.

33:25.717 --> 33:27.742
You have any kids? Why
do you need to know that?

33:27.819 --> 33:29.719
We don't,
the lab does.

33:31.389 --> 33:33.914
Sure. I got one son.

33:34.192 --> 33:35.352
Date of birth?

33:35.427 --> 33:39.921
1971. No, wait, '70.

33:40.532 --> 33:41.794
City of residence?

33:41.866 --> 33:45.063
I'm not sure. He was my
kid from my first wife.

33:45.136 --> 33:47.696
Well, how about the last time
you talked to him, where was he?

33:47.772 --> 33:52.072
He was 13,
he called me.

33:52.544 --> 33:54.239
He was still
in New Rochelle.

33:54.312 --> 33:56.303
Kid's mother was
getting remarried.

33:56.381 --> 33:58.645
Her husband
wanted to adopt him.

33:58.717 --> 34:02.448
He had this crazy idea that
I wouldn't be his dad anymore.

34:02.520 --> 34:03.680
I hope you
set him straight.

34:03.755 --> 34:07.054
I told him that a piece of
paper doesn't mean squat.

34:08.426 --> 34:13.295
He was my flesh and blood, my
DNA, can't run away from it.

34:14.666 --> 34:19.069
He got the best of me the
night I rolled off his mother.

34:24.175 --> 34:25.505
Open wide.

34:27.045 --> 34:29.536
I saw right through
that DNA crap.

34:29.614 --> 34:32.844
If I hadn't volunteered, they'd use it
as an excuse to crawl right up my ass!

34:32.917 --> 34:36.181
Frank, relax. They've
already indicted somebody.

34:36.254 --> 34:38.380
Some guy named
Keith Durbin.

34:45.897 --> 34:48.228
McNare's DNA was
a five-point match

34:48.299 --> 34:50.130
to the sample
from the crime scene.

34:50.201 --> 34:52.567
Same as his son.
What progress.

34:53.271 --> 34:57.833
We now have two suspects, each of whom
create reasonable doubt for the other.

34:57.909 --> 35:01.743
If Durbin told us what he saw
in that photo when he was 7,

35:02.046 --> 35:03.604
maybe we'd get somewhere with McNare.

35:03.681 --> 35:05.239
What are the
chances of that?

35:05.316 --> 35:08.752
When he was 13, he realized
that he was sexually aroused

35:08.820 --> 35:13.519
by the image of a woman being
tortured and murdered by his father.

35:13.591 --> 35:15.889
Now, that's knowledge that
I can't imagine living with.

35:15.960 --> 35:17.587
He's not responsible
for her death.

35:17.662 --> 35:19.994
He believes that he
inherited his father's evil.

35:20.064 --> 35:22.624
And he believes that because
his father told him as much.

35:22.700 --> 35:27.831
He just thinks it's a matter of time until
he becomes the killer that his father is.

35:27.906 --> 35:30.101
It's irrational,
but it's the one thing

35:30.175 --> 35:32.643
that he most deeply
believes about himself.

35:32.710 --> 35:34.302
He probably thinks
if he tells anybody

35:34.379 --> 35:36.472
his father killed
that girl in 1977,

35:36.548 --> 35:38.812
we'll lock him up
along with his dad.

35:38.883 --> 35:42.250
Well, how do we liberate
Mr. Durbin from that belief?

35:43.621 --> 35:46.556
Well, his father may
be the only one who can.

35:47.559 --> 35:49.288
He said all he's gonna
say about the charges.

35:49.360 --> 35:54.423
Well, actually, we were hoping
for information on another case.

35:55.333 --> 35:57.494
If he gives us
some help on this case,

35:57.569 --> 36:01.562
then the DA will give him some
consideration on the other ones.

36:01.639 --> 36:03.436
He's not a suspect
in this new case?

36:03.508 --> 36:07.638
He would have been 7 years old at
the time, that's what I'm saying.

36:11.382 --> 36:12.906
Kimberly Lange.

36:14.085 --> 36:17.384
She's from your old stomping
ground in New Rochelle.

36:17.755 --> 36:22.158
She disappeared in 1977, her
remains were found in 1983.

36:23.261 --> 36:26.287
Is there anything you
can tell me about this?

36:28.833 --> 36:32.360
His flesh, his blood.
You're just like him.

36:34.539 --> 36:37.440
That is what you
believe, isn't it, Keith?

36:38.109 --> 36:39.872
Who's he talking about?

36:39.944 --> 36:41.172
Nothing. Nobody.

36:41.246 --> 36:44.340
If your family ever found out, your
mother, your sister, your stepfather,

36:44.415 --> 36:45.609
they'd write you off,
wouldn't they?

36:45.683 --> 36:46.672
I don't know anything.

36:46.751 --> 36:47.911
'Cause it's just
a matter of time

36:47.986 --> 36:51.786
until you become him,
until you do what he does.

36:56.027 --> 36:58.359
Is that what
you believe, Keith?

37:01.799 --> 37:03.824
You need
to see something.

37:09.440 --> 37:11.169
There he is, Keith.

37:13.177 --> 37:18.513
The man whose perversions have haunted
you, overwhelmed you all these years.

37:19.517 --> 37:20.506
My dad?

37:20.585 --> 37:21.882
Came here
to talk about you.

37:21.953 --> 37:24.387
You wanna hear
what he has to say?

37:27.225 --> 37:28.283
<i>What was that?</i>

37:28.359 --> 37:30.589
<i>They're doing renovations next door.</i>

37:31.896 --> 37:35.297
<i>Let's talk about
your son, Keith.</i>

37:36.834 --> 37:39.894
<i>After we got your DNA, we
tracked down his whereabouts...</i>

37:39.971 --> 37:42.132
<i>He's the guy you should
be looking at for this.</i>

37:42.507 --> 37:44.634
<i>Well, it's funny
you should say that.</i>

37:44.709 --> 37:46.904
<i>We talked to his mother.
