37:46.978 --> 37:51.540
<i>she remembered him dressing up his
teddy bear in her bra and panties</i>

37:51.616 --> 37:54.710
<i>and tying a little
string to the bear's foot.</i>

37:54.786 --> 37:57.380
<i>Well,
there you go.</i>

37:57.455 --> 37:59.855
<i>Pantywaist little pervert.</i>

38:00.959 --> 38:03.519
<i>His mother did it to him,
all that mollycoddling.</i>

38:03.595 --> 38:05.085
<i>How do you figure?</i>

38:05.163 --> 38:10.100
<i>She would let little Keith sleep
in the bed with us until he was 5.</i>

38:11.469 --> 38:14.404
<i>That's not normal,
not for a boy.</i>

38:15.206 --> 38:18.300
<i>What I don't
understand, Frank,</i>

38:18.376 --> 38:20.503
<i>didn't you tell him
when he was 13</i>

38:20.578 --> 38:22.842
<i>that everything
he was he owed to you?</i>

38:23.648 --> 38:25.309
<i>The flesh
and blood speech,</i>

38:25.383 --> 38:28.978
<i>how he couldn't run away from the
great genetic gift you gave him?</i>

38:29.053 --> 38:32.022
<i>I just wanted to get him off the phone.</i>

38:32.757 --> 38:34.657
<i>He was all upset
about being adopted.</i>

38:34.726 --> 38:37.957
<i>We heard you were in a
hurry to sign off on that.</i>

38:38.630 --> 38:42.088
<i>Was it because you'd be off
the hook for child support?</i>

38:43.968 --> 38:46.562
<i>These cops,
they're geniuses.</i>

38:49.474 --> 38:53.433
<i>You know, sometimes I'd look
into that mewly little kid's face</i>

38:54.512 --> 38:57.481
<i>and wonder if he even
was my flesh and blood.</i>

38:59.217 --> 39:02.277
<i>That mother of his?
I wouldn't put it past her.</i>

39:07.825 --> 39:10.919
You still think that
you're anything like him?

39:11.295 --> 39:14.059
This cruel
and uncaring man.

39:14.132 --> 39:17.727
He has no guilt and no shame.
You're nothing like him.

39:19.504 --> 39:21.301
Do you think that
you're the first son

39:21.372 --> 39:24.864
that's afraid of becoming
his imperfect father? No.

39:25.643 --> 39:28.976
His flaws, his sins, they're
his, they're not yours!

39:31.482 --> 39:33.416
That image?
That image,

39:35.053 --> 39:38.853
the image that's dominated
your thoughts, he created it!

39:39.824 --> 39:43.487
Keith, it's time, man,
it's time to spit it out.

39:47.432 --> 39:49.229
Tell us what you saw.

39:53.771 --> 39:56.001
Were you in your
father's car?

39:58.209 --> 39:59.972
You find something?

40:04.682 --> 40:06.479
Did you find a photo?

40:09.120 --> 40:10.109
Yeah.

40:10.188 --> 40:11.348
What was in the photo?

40:15.660 --> 40:17.287
There was a girl.

40:20.098 --> 40:25.559
She was tied up,
like the other girls.

40:27.605 --> 40:29.129
She was afraid.

40:31.843 --> 40:36.371
We're gonna need
exact details.

40:38.182 --> 40:45.111
She was wearing a white
bra and white panties.

40:48.893 --> 40:51.623
She had a mark
on her right shoulder.

40:52.997 --> 40:54.430
A birthmark.

40:55.500 --> 40:56.831
What else?

41:00.037 --> 41:02.005
She was tied
with rope.

41:02.073 --> 41:06.703
Around her hands.
And around her ankle.

41:08.546 --> 41:10.013
And her neck.

41:12.216 --> 41:14.081
A blue and white rope.

41:16.387 --> 41:19.322
I didn't know why she
was tied up like that.

41:20.625 --> 41:24.755
Why Dad had her picture
hidden in the glove box.

41:27.999 --> 41:30.559
I knew I wasn't
supposed to look at it,

41:30.635 --> 41:35.732
but I couldn't help it.
I couldn't...

41:40.978 --> 41:44.744
I do have a... Oh, well,
look who's joining the party.

41:45.049 --> 41:47.176
Have you got your
list of questions?

41:47.251 --> 41:48.684
Just answers, Jake.

41:49.520 --> 41:50.646
What was all that
racket out there?

41:50.721 --> 41:53.781
That was the sound of the
hammer coming down on you, Jake.

41:53.858 --> 41:54.950
Stop calling
me that.

41:55.026 --> 41:57.290
Your son.
He gave you up.

41:57.361 --> 41:58.885
Kimberly Lange.

42:00.298 --> 42:03.131
He found your Polaroid
of her in your car.

42:03.935 --> 42:06.199
He hasn't been in my car since he was 8.

42:06.270 --> 42:07.498
You're gonna believe
what a kid saw?

42:07.572 --> 42:10.166
He remembers everything.

42:10.975 --> 42:13.341
Everything that
excited his dad.

42:13.911 --> 42:17.642
Right down to the color of the rope
that you used on her, blue and white?

42:17.715 --> 42:21.412
Same color of the fibers found
embedded in Kimberly's wrist.

42:21.485 --> 42:23.419
I gotta figure
this out for you, huh?

42:23.487 --> 42:25.455
The kid probably read
about it in the papers.

42:25.523 --> 42:27.320
That detail was never made public.

42:27.391 --> 42:29.359
It was never
in the papers.

42:33.698 --> 42:35.461
That little bastard.

42:35.533 --> 42:37.660
He's free of you
now, Frank.

42:39.403 --> 42:44.636
Cast you out of his head.
Out of his head.

42:45.176 --> 42:46.803
Get up, big man,
you're under arrest

42:46.878 --> 42:49.438
for the murder
of Kimberly Lange.

42:51.249 --> 42:52.716
Six counts
of first-degree murder,

42:52.783 --> 42:56.344
and you'll be hearing from
the authorities in New Jersey.

42:58.756 --> 43:00.883
You nosy little deviant.

43:00.958 --> 43:03.222
Your own father,
how could you?

43:03.294 --> 43:04.488
How could you, Dad?

43:05.763 --> 43:09.494
Dad? You're no
son of mine.

43:12.303 --> 43:15.067
That's the nicest thing
he could have said to him.

